data.text:
Anna Tsuchiya - Debut Full-Length Album

A model, actress (including her breakthrough film "Kamikaze Girls (Shimotsuma Monogatari)," and vocalist, Anna Tsuchiya isn't just talented, she dominates at everything she does. And now that she's smashed the airwaves with her single "rose" for the anime series "Nana," she's braced to release her first full-length album!

Her first full-length is due August 2, and is set to include her singles "rose" and "Lovin' you." Anna's work is already gathering praise from artists across the musical spectrum, with everyone from Josh Freese from A Perfect Circle to Avril Lavigne guitarist Michael Ward backing her up. Did we mention that Guns 'n' Roses members Duff McKagan and Matt Sorum are both in her backing band?

Order now to get the CD+DVD version of the album, which includes a bonus DVD with Anna Tsuchiya's complete music video collection. Regular edition (no DVD) available as well.
